@startuml fig-ipv4-vs-ipv6
'A4 Landscape
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam shadowing false

title IPv4 vs IPv6 Comparison

rectangle "IPv4" as v4 #E3F2FD {
    rectangle "32-bit address\n4.3 billion addresses\n192.168.1.1" as v4addr #BBDEFB
    rectangle "Header: 20-60 bytes\nChecksum, Options" as v4hdr #BBDEFB
    rectangle "NAT required\nAddress exhaustion" as v4nat #FFCDD2
}

rectangle "IPv6" as v6 #E8F5E9 {
    rectangle "128-bit address\n340 undecillion\n2001:db8::1" as v6addr #C8E6C9
    rectangle "Header: 40 bytes fixed\nNo checksum, Extensions" as v6hdr #C8E6C9
    rectangle "No NAT needed\nEnd-to-end connectivity" as v6nat #C8E6C9
}

note bottom of v4
    IPv4 Address:
    Dotted decimal
    192.168.1.1
    
    Subnet: /24
    Broadcast: Yes
end note

note bottom of v6
    IPv6 Address:
    Colon hexadecimal
    2001:0db8:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0001
    2001:db8::1 (compressed)
    
    Prefix: /64
    No broadcast (multicast only)
end note

note as N1
    Key Differences:
    | Feature | IPv4 | IPv6 |
    | Address bits | 32 | 128 |
    | Notation | Decimal | Hex |
    | Autoconfigure | DHCP | SLAAC |
    | IPsec | Optional | Built-in |
    | Fragmentation | Routers | Source only |
end note

